    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-breast-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>roughly</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>garlic </strong>roughly</p><p>Peel your <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and chop roughly (or grate)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-breast-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Split open your <strong>cardamom pods</strong>, removing the black inner seeds</p><p>Grind them slightly in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong>, and heat a dry pan over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once warm, add the <strong>cardamom seeds</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong> ground turmeric</strong></p><p>Toast the spices for 30 seconds, then add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> to the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-breast-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and<strong> </strong>a squeeze of your <strong>lime juice</strong> and continue to cook for 1 min</p><p>Add in your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong>,<strong> ground almonds</strong> and your <strong>honey</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 2 min</p><p>Transfer the mixture to a processor, reserve the pan and blitz until smooth paste - this is your <strong>curry paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-breast-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>chicken</strong> into strips</p><p>Return the pan back to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the chicken and cook for 2 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-breast-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>curry paste</strong> to the chicken with 180ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and cook on a medium-low heat for 10 min, then remove the lid and reduce for 5 min further or until thickened and the chicken is cooked (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-breast-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Add them to a pot with 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 7 min over a high heat or until they are tender</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-breast-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>turmeric chicken curry</strong> over the <strong>cauliflower</strong> <strong>rice</strong> and <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
